HEADWORD: Pedestaled
<hw>Ped"es*taled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Placed on, or
supported by, a pedestal; figuratively, exalted.</def>
<rj><au>Hawthorne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Pedestaled</qex> haply in a palace court.</q>
<rj><qau>Keats.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

